    <div class="container body-content">

        <h2>Snackbar / Toast</h2>
        <p>Snackbars are often used as a tooltips/popups to show a message at the bottom of the screen.</p>
        <p>Click on the button to show the snackbar. It will disappear after 3 seconds.</p>

        <button onclick="ShowSnackbarSuccess()">Show Snackbar success</button>
        <button onclick="ShowSnackbarError()">Show Snackbar failure</button>
        <button onclick="ShowSnackbarMessage()">Show Snackbar message</button>


        <div id="snackbar-success">
            Some text some message.. some text some textSome text some message.. some text some textSome text some message.. some text some text
        </div>
        <div id="snackbar-error">
            Some text some message.. some text some textSome text some message.. some text some textSome text some message.. some text some text
        </div>
        <div id="snackbar-message">
            Some text some message.. some text some textSome text some message.. some text some textSome text some message.. some text some text
        </div>
    </div>


<style>

    #snackbar-success,
    #snackbar-error,
    #snackbar-message {
        visibility: hidden;
        width: 100%;
        margin-left: 0;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 10px;
        position: fixed;
        z-index: 2500;
        left: 0;
        top: 20vh;
        font-size: 17px;
    }

    #snackbar-success {
        background-color: #6dbd28;
        color: #fff;
    }

    #snackbar-error{
        background-color:#ff0000;
        color: #fff;
    }

    #snackbar-message{
        background-color:#AFB20C;
        color: #fff;
    }

    #snackbar-success.show,
    #snackbar-error.show,
    #snackbar-message.show{
        visibility: visible;
    }
</style>


